Description:
Dapper Domain delight!
Surrounded by stately period homes in a timeless Domain location, this elevated 1 bedroom (plus study) solid-brick apartment will delight with far-reaching space.
Under soaring ceilings, discover spacious open-plan living and dining with built-in cabinetry, and a separate, sparkling kitchen with relaxed, treetop views.
Comprehensive features include a deluxe bathroom with a bath and laundry capability, off-street parking, and a handy study for all those home office duties.
• 1 large bedroom with BIR
• Secure intercom entry
• Tiled entrance
• Large, south-facing picture windows throughout with leafy views
Prominently positioned on the first floor of a well-maintained block, walk to the greenery of Fawkner Park, Toorak Road shopping and public transport options.
For more information, please contact Shawn White today.

Description:
A contemporary sanctuary and an effervescent lifestyle
Immeasurable comfort, sophisticated style, and a staggering location, this impeccably maintained one-bedroom apartment has all the wow factors to incorporate into an astute investment portfolio. Offering an effervescent inner-city lifestyle, the spoils of exquisite cuisine and boutique shopping are at the doorstep, alongside endless recreation, city-bound transport and everyday services, creating an enviable environment for non-stop tenancy.
Enjoying a magnificent, leafy outlook toward Fawkner Park, the home is a perfect sanctuary from a bustling lifestyle. A perfect integration of indoor and outdoor living, the generous living and dining space flows onto a wide private balcony, serviced by a sleek kitchen dressed in gloss cabinetry and stone tops, with a full-appointment of quality appliances. Fully-furnished with contemporary styling, the home delivers immediate luxury and relaxation, providing residents’ facilities including a swimming pool, steam room and gymnasium.
Complete with a large robed bedroom, European laundry, and secure parking, this impeccable home offers instant security with a lease in place until August 2019. Perfectly located just minutes from the Yarra River’s parklands and walking trails, the CBD’s infinite entertainment destinations, and Richmond’s sporting precinct.

Description:
Contemporary Courtyard Apartment with Private Access
A recent renovation has transformed this courtyard apartment in an unbeatable location into a superb inner city sanctuary. Set in a boutique low-rise security complex within tree-lined Tivoli Road, the sleek elevated ground floor apartment is footsteps from trams, the renowned Tivoli Bakery, cafés, restaurants, wine bars and shops plus South Yarra Station and the Yarra River are an easy stroll away. Boasting private access into the home from the courtyard garden and its very own carspace right beside it, the interior comprises of an open plan design showcasing a contemporary kitchen (DW) flowing to the living and dining zone which spills out to the generous and very private decked courtyard, perfect for entertaining. Two sun-filled, spacious bedrooms are fitted with mirrored built in robes and the central bathroom oozes sophistication. Concealed laundry facilities, heating/cooling, bamboo flooring throughout and nothing left to do but move in or lease out ensure instant appeal.

Description:
Renovated, light-filled living in one of South Yarra's best streets!
Wonderfully renovated apartment offering stellar open plan living with sensational natural light. Freshly painted and offering sleek new flooring, it’s the ultimate city pad that’s ready to move straight in. Set at the end of a beautiful tree-lined cul-de-sac filled with prestigious and grand mansion style properties, this 2 bedroom retreat is sure to appeal to young professionals, an investor or anyone who wants to live the vibrant South Yarra lifestyle. You'll love the airy layout of the spacious living and dining, which enters out to a relaxing undercover balcony offering green views of a striking Magnolia tree. A separate kitchen has been updated to suit those who love to cook from home. Both bedrooms are generous in size and are saturated in natural light and boast terrific storage options. The bathroom has a designer edge featuring Moroccan-inspired tiling which perfectly complements the timber vanity. There is a bath, laundry facilities and separate WC. Mod cons include a split system cooling/heating unit, and secure intercom entry.
Enjoy your morning run at Fawkner Park or The Tan, before grabbing a coffee at one of the many cafes nearby and catching the tram to work.
This apartment is in a first class location, just a stone's throw to shops and restaurants on Toorak Road, while you're also near Chapel Street shopping, Royal Botanic Gardens, Domain Road cafes, buses, and South Yarra Station.

Description:
Exceptional Elegance and Exclusivity
Exclusively situated in a tightly held cul de sac, this utterly captivating c1920's solid brick residence's unforgettable dimensions deliver immeasurable family lifestyle appeal walking distance to elite schools, the Botanic Gardens, MCG, AAMI stadium, Tennis Centre, the Yarra and the restaurants and boutiques on Toorak Rd.
Distinguished by timber floors, gracious proportions and ornate ceilings, the imposing reception hall, beautiful sitting room with open fireplace and glorious formal dining room with gas fire make an irresistible first impression. Bathed in natural light, the sleek gourmet kitchen featuring stone benches and a living area with open fireplace opens through a series of French doors to a private north-facing bluestone paved terrace with plunge pool. A gorgeous bedroom with robes and open fire, a study/4th bedroom and two lavish marble bathrooms are downstairs while two additional double bedrooms with built in robes and a third stylish bathroom are on the level above.
Framed by picturesque established gardens, this stunning home is appointed with an alarm, video intercom, cellar, laundry, carport, additional car-space and auto gate. Land: 613sqm approx.

Description:
The Millswyn - Sensational Style and Lifestyle
Situated in arguably Melbourne's most desired and prestigious location "The Domain Precinct", Pask Groups presents The Millswyn.
Upon entering Millswyn Street the carved architecture of the isernia limestone façade commands attention with timeless poise. Inspired by its locale and a sense of grand sophistication, Millswyn Private Residences embody the Rob Mills ethos of exceptional architecture, Paul Bangay landscaping uniting to create an unparalleled lifestyle.
A commitment to craftsmanship without compromise, where light and quality of space is celebrated on a grand scale, residence three represents an exquisite marble kitchen and scullery with family and dining area surrounded by full height window walls, opening to a private lush garden terrace, a palatial main bedroom suite (WIR & ensuite), complimented by two further bedrooms, central bathroom and fitted study.
Just a short stroll to the restaurants and shops on Domain and Toorak Roads the residence also features separate laundry, lift access, 3.2m ceiling heights, remote blinds, private basement garaging for 2 cars plus private storage.

Description:
Stunning Victorian Period Style Home on 436sqm Corner Position
Exclusively positioned in South Yarra just a short stroll from the Jam Factory and Chapel Street shopping precinct, this Victorian period inspired home was solidly built in 1985 and is spacious enough to accommodate the modern family looking for immeasurable inner urban lifestyle. With a huge north facing backyard with a spacious double garage, this single level residence provides options for long term investors wanting to secure a large block of land in a bluechip location, renovators or developers wanting to capitalise on the huge 436sqm (9.3m x 47.1m) corner position in the NRZ3 zone (No Heritage Overlay and No Easement) for a single luxury home or multiple luxury townhouses (STCA).
Behind its appealing facade you will find a central hallway with 3 large bedrooms, 2 spacious formal and dining rooms, central bathroom with an additional powder room, decking which flows out to the large backyard, which has been meticulously looked after and a huge double garage with your own laneway access down Wisewould Lane. The home also features art deco details, high ceilings and upon walking through the residence you will immediately notice the quality of the build being of the highest standards.
Walk to absolutely everything in a few minutes including The Jam Factory, Chapel Street cafes/shops, Prahran Market and trams/train stations- Contact Scott today on (03) 9568 8000 to secure this fantastic opportunity!
*All enquiries must include a phone number

Description:
Stylish One Bedder with Car Space
A fabulous totally convenient position walking distance to South Yarra Station, Toorak Road trams, Chapel Street, plus an abundance of cafes and boutique shops all very close by. This top floor corner "lilli" apartment is an absolute gem and a perfect entry level for first home buyers and investors alike.
Positioned on the sixteenth floor with easterly suburban views through to the ranges you will love the easy living design featuring a tiled entry through to the open plan living area that extends out to the covered balcony with a built in barbecue. The kitchen area is very well appointed with oven, gas cook top, integrated dish-draw, stylish range-hood and plenty of cupboard space including a pantry.The separate double bedroom has built in robes and the chick tiled bathroom features a large shower.
Additional features include secure intercom entry, an elegant building foyer, lift access, heating/cooling, Euro style laundry and a secure car space on title.

Description:
Unbelievable Uninterrupted Views of the City and Parklands
You will be impressed as soon as you walk into this contemporary apartment with amazing views across Parklands, Yarra River and the Melbourne city skyline with fantastic entertainer’s terrace most would envy.
This bright North facing apartment offers good security entry with lift access. The entrance hallway leads to a modern stone kitchen with Miele appliances and ample cupboards space and study area. The light filled living and dining room has floor to ceiling windows to appreciate the views whilst relaxing on the lounge and opens onto large undercover terrace. Both bedrooms have built in robes and enjoy the city views (main with ensuite bathroom), european laundry, sparkling central bathroom and one car park on title with adjoining motorcycle space. The building offers luxury common lounges, outside heated pool and spa, gymnasium and terrace area with BBQ facilities.
The location speaks for itself only a short walk to South Yarra train station and trams, Yarra River walking track on both sides leading to the Botanic Gardens and city and close to all shopping boutiques, cafes and restaurants South Yarra has to offer.

Description:
Art Deco allure, location and lifestyle
Superbly positioned just moments from Toorak and Hawksburn villages, this two bedroom Art Deco apartment presents a rare opportunity. One of only four units on a sizeable block, the 1930s double brick residence's well presented interior, highlighted by French doors and ornate ceilings, features a delightfully proportioned living room with an open fireplace. Complete with a casual dining space, a generous kitchen is fitted with ample storage and a suite of quality appliances. A grand main bedroom with extensive built in robes enjoys leafy outlooks and leads to a private and light filled study creating a quiet retreat. Comforts extend to a spacious second bedroom complemented by a central bathroom. Other features include ducted heating, a single car garage, storage, laundry facilities and a gracious main entrance and staircase with original, patterned terrazzo flooring. A superior location puts Como Park, Chapel Street dining precinct, Hawksburn Station and trams within easy reach.

Description:
Art Deco Living 1 bedroom Apartment in Prime Location
Phone enquiry code for this property: 9235
Inspection by Appointment Only
If you are looking for style, character, comfort and a fabulous location, you will be delighted to own this beautiful Howard Lawson Art Deco 1 bedroom Apartment in a boutique block of only 10, complete with off street parking and a large communal garden and rooftop terrace.
Entry hall, spacious living with a large separate bedroom with bay windows plus separate kitchen and fully renovated bathroom with luxury modern appointments
Designed by prominent Melbourne architect Howard Lawson in the late 1930's famous for many South Yarra icons the full renovation only completed in late 2016 - absolutely nothing more to do and keeping the period style and feel with modern comforts and appointments.
Along with the 2 spacious rooms and private bathroom and kitchen, the property also offers the use of a large shared garden, rooftop terrace with outdoor tables and BBQ while you take in the great views of the river and the city of Melbourne.
Located at the end of one of South Yarra's most well known no through roads, lined with magnificent trees and with an original pathway leading down to Alexandra Avenue for the bus to the city or for walks to The Royal Botanical Gardens or a little further to the MCG, Rod Laver Arena and the Melbourne CBD all along the Yarra River Trails or to Como Park and our local cafe Canteen on the riverside, or yet again to Toorak and Hawksburn Villages.
Then there is a 5 minute walk along Toorak Road to our famous Chapel Street to explore for fabulous shopping, dining or just hanging out.
Location, Location, Location - a secure investment and rare find in this tightly held inner Melbourne location.
